# Dalny, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Dalny (; , Arğı) is a rural locality (a khutor) in Shingak-Kulsky Selsoviet, Chishminsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The village has 3 streets and, as of 2010, a population of 48.
Geography
Dalny is located 46 km southwest of Chishmy, the district's administrative centre. Verkhny is the nearest rural locality.
